  "text": "The effects of p,p´-DDT on the LH/hCG receptor (LH/hCGR), a closely related receptor that belongs to the same family as the FSHR [CITATION_1] , were also analyzed. In CHO cell lines stably transfected with the human LH/hCGR (CHO-LH/hCGR) [CITATION_2] , p,p´-DDT decreased the cAMP production stimulated by hCG at a concentration of 0.01 IU/mL, in a dose-dependent manner, to 80 ± 3.7% of the response in the absence of p,p´-DDT ( Figure 2B) . The response to 100 IU/mL hCG was also increased in response to p,p´-DDT, but the increase was significant only at the lowest dose of p,p´-DDT (10 -7 M) ( Figure 2B ). Interestingly, p,p´-DDT decreased the basal activity of LH/hCGR by 50 ± 9%.",
